Those who did manage to get into the Space, including several Verge staffers, said it kicked off with lo-fi techno playing from Trump’s account for roughly 30 minutes.

18 minutes after the conversation was supposed to begin, Musk claimed that X was the target of a “massive DDOS attack” that had made it impossible for the Space to proceed as planned.

The rest of X appears to be working normally, however, and a source at the company confirmed to The Verge that there wasn’t actually a denial-of-service attack. Another X staffer said there was a “99 percent” chance Elon was lying about an attack.

https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/12/24219121/donald-trump-elon-musk-interview-x-twitter-crashes

Musk And Trump On The Economy
Musk and Trump exchange views on what's wrong with the economy. Musk proposes a "government efficiency commission." He says he'd be happy to help out with that.

https://www.investors.com/news/donald-trump-elon-musk-tesla-stock-truth-social/

https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/politics/total-disaster-elon-musk-s-trump-interview-flops-immediately-with-tech-glitches-he-claims-massive-ddos-attack/ar-AA1oGsGV</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Epx8lSb.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/uXlmgqo</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jbelkin]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I’m going to help regardless of what may come</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/KbCzsP3</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/93CcX7C.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>My next door neighbor needs a new heart. He was told by one major university hospital he isn’t a good candidate. He will likely not receive a transplant. 

I have been sneaking over to mow his lawn, trim, and do basic maintenance he is in too poor health to do for himself. I have been there, with my kidney failure, lung issues, plus many more medical problems. 

I don’t ask for anything in return, as I have had help every time I have had such struggles. A feeling of obligation towards a debt I can never fully repay to those who helped me. 

He is originally from a southern state in the USA and wasn’t prepared for the snow and ice of the north. He and I chat about the snow, he is planning on buying a snowblower, I told him if he buys it, I’ll take care of his driveway for him. I gave my snowblower to a couple in need when I moved away, but was forced to move back.

I fear he won’t make it through the winter as is. He is in very poor health. If I had the money to purchase one, I would and rather he just focus on his health. He is talking about a snowblower that is about $100, but I don’t think he realizes that particular model won’t be powerful enough to take care of the job. 

Doing what I can to try and save up closer to something in the  $500-$800 range, but I am overdrawn in my checking only 4 days after payday. So it hasn’t gone well. 

No matter what happens, I’ll manage and help him as best I can. I just worry about the man’s health. I would rather he not waste his money on a machine that won’t be able to handle the task. I am afraid that, come winter, I will go out to find him passed out or dead in the snow, having tried to shovel it himself. 

Winter is months away, but…

… anyways. So that’s where my head is at today. Mowed for him the other day and he was home to catch and thank me. $100 snowblower isn’t going to do much of anything where I live when it snows. He is a good man, younger than I thought too. I can only hope he gets a chance… no matter the case, I’ll do what I can.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/KbCzsP3</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Hellstorm99]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Non coalescence of water</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/O4pu3hk</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/2ASN00c.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/O4pu3hk</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[DOcelot]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Bless em</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/7SiO7mO</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MFw6soq.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/7SiO7mO</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[roaduardo]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Russia complained that its 'peaceful' people don't deserve to be invaded</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/fbU1YN7</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/UDKg5aS.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Russia complained about Ukraine advances into the Kursk region, calling the people there "peaceful."

